2947 \param Width Width in units set by Unit
2948 \param Pod U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing first the PenData flags then a U_PMF_PENOPTIONALDATA object (the second part
2949 may be an empty if Flags is 0)
2950
2951
2952 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.33, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPenData Object
2953*/
2954U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMF_PENDATA_set(uint32_t Unit, U_FLOAT Width, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Pod){
2955 if(Pod && ((Pod->Type != U_PMF_PENOPTIONALDATA_OID0x02020234) || Pod->Used < 4))return(NULL((void*)0));
2956 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {

2962 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
2963 };
2964 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMF_PENDATA_OID0x02020233, List);

2970 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error. Returned PO contains first the Flags, then the PO proper.
2971 \param Flags Determines which of the values are stored.
2972 \param Tm U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX object (Transformation matrix)
2973 \param StartCap LineCapType enumeration
2974 \param EndCap LineCapType enumeration
2975 \param Join LineJoinType enumeration
2976 \param MiterLimit Maximum (miter length / line width)
2977 \param Style LineStyle enumeration

2979 \param DLOffset Distance line start to first dash start
2980 \param DLData U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_DASHEDLINEDATA object Dash and space widths
2981 \param PenAlignment PenAlignment enumeration
2982 \param CmpndLineData U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_COMPOUNDLINEDATA object Compount Line (parallel lines drawn instead of one)
2983 \param CSCapData U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_CUSTOMSTARTCAPDATA object Custom start cap
2984 \param CECapData U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_CUSTOMENDCAPDATA object Custom end cap
2985
2986
2987 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.34, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPenOptionalData Object
2988*/
2989U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMF_PENOPTIONALDATA_set(uint32_t Flags, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Tm, int32_t StartCap, int32_t EndCap, uint32_t Join,
2990 U_FLOAT MiterLimit, int32_t Style, int32_t DLCap, U_FLOAT DLOffset,
2991 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *DLData, int32_t PenAlignment, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *CmpndLineData, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *CSCapData,
2992 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *CECapData
2993 ){
2994
2995 if((Flags & U_PD_Transform0x0001) && (!Tm || (Tm->Type != U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX_OID0x02020247)) )return(NULL((void*)0));
2996 if((Flags & U_PD_DLData0x0100) && (!DLData || (DLData->Type != U_PMF_DASHEDLINEDATA_OID0x02020216)) )return(NULL((void*)0));
2997 if((Flags & U_PD_CLData0x0400) && (!CmpndLineData || (CmpndLineData->Type != U_PMF_COMPOUNDLINEDATA_OID0x02020209)) )return(NULL((void*)0));
2998 if((Flags & U_PD_CustomStartCap0x0800) && (!CSCapData || (CSCapData->Type != U_PMF_CUSTOMSTARTCAPDATA_OID0x02020215)))return(NULL((void*)0));
2999 if((Flags & U_PD_CustomEndCap0x1000) && (!CECapData || (CECapData->Type != U_PMF_CUSTOMENDCAPDATA_OID0x02020211)) )return(NULL((void*)0));
3000
3001 /* prepend the Flags field to the PseudoObject proper */
3002 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3003 {&Flags, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3004 {((Flags & U_PD_Transform0x0001) ? Tm->Data : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_Transform0x0001) ? Tm->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3005 {((Flags & U_PD_StartCap0x0002 ) ? (char *)&StartCap : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_StartCap0x0002 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3006 {((Flags & U_PD_EndCap0x0004 ) ? (char *)&EndCap : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_EndCap0x0004 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3007 {((Flags & U_PD_Join0x0008 ) ? (char *)&Join : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_Join0x0008 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3008 {((Flags & U_PD_MiterLimit0x0010 ) ? (char *)&MiterLimit : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_MiterLimit0x0010 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3009 {((Flags & U_PD_LineStyle0x0020 ) ? (char *)&Style : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_LineStyle0x0020 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3010 {((Flags & U_PD_DLCap0x0040 ) ? (char *)&DLCap : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_DLCap0x0040 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3011 {((Flags & U_PD_DLOffset0x0080 ) ? (char *)&DLOffset : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_DLOffset0x0080 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3012 {((Flags & U_PD_DLData0x0100 ) ? DLData->Data : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_DLData0x0100 ) ? DLData->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3013 {((Flags & U_PD_NonCenter0x0200 ) ? (char *)&PenAlignment : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_NonCenter0x0200 ) ? 4 : 0), 1, U_LE1},
3014 {((Flags & U_PD_CLData0x0400 ) ? CmpndLineData->Data : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_CLData0x0400 ) ? CmpndLineData->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3015 {((Flags & U_PD_CustomStartCap0x0800) ? CSCapData->Data : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_CustomStartCap0x0800) ? CSCapData->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3016 {((Flags & U_PD_CustomEndCap0x1000 ) ? CECapData->Data : NULL((void*)0)), ((Flags & U_PD_CustomEndCap0x1000 ) ? CECapData->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3017 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}

3020 return(po);

3060
3061/**
3062 \brief Create and set an ARRAY of U_PMF_POINTR objects
3063 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
3064 \param Elements Number of pairs of points in Coords
3065 \param Coords Array of X,Y pairs. These are absolute coordinates, they are converted to Relative here.
3066
3067 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.37, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPointR Object
3068*/
3069U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMF_POINTR_set(uint32_t Elements, const U_PMF_POINTF *Coords){
3070 int X,Y;
3071 U_FLOAT Xf,Yf;
3072 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *poi;
3073 /* Worst case scenario it is 4 bytes per coord, plus the count */
3074 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PO_create(NULL((void*)0), 4 + 4*Elements, 0, U_PMF_POINTR_OID0x02020237); /* not exactly an array, so no U_PMF_ARRAY_OID */
3075 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *holdpo = po;
3076 if(!po)goto end;
3077
3078 poi = U_PMF_4NUM_set(Elements);
3079 po = U_PO_append(po, poi->Data, poi->Used);
3080 U_PO_free(&poi);
3081 if(!po)goto end;
3082
3083 for(Xf = Yf = 0.0 ;Elements; Elements--, Coords++){
3084 Xf = U_ROUND(Coords->X)( (Coords->X) > 0 ? floor((Coords->X)+0.5) : ( (Coords
->X) < 0 ? -floor(-(Coords->X)+0.5) : (Coords->X)
) ) - Xf;
3085 Yf = U_ROUND(Coords->Y)( (Coords->Y) > 0 ? floor((Coords->Y)+0.5) : ( (Coords
->Y) < 0 ? -floor(-(Coords->Y)+0.5) : (Coords->Y)
) ) - Yf;
3086 X = ( Xf >= UINT16_MAX(65535) ? UINT16_MAX(65535) : ( Xf <= INT16_MIN(-32767-1) ? INT16_MIN(-32767-1) : Xf));
3087 Y = ( Yf >= UINT16_MAX(65535) ? UINT16_MAX(65535) : ( Yf <= INT16_MIN(-32767-1) ? INT16_MIN(-32767-1) : Yf));
3088 Xf = U_ROUND(Coords->X)( (Coords->X) > 0 ? floor((Coords->X)+0.5) : ( (Coords
->X) < 0 ? -floor(-(Coords->X)+0.5) : (Coords->X)
) );
3089 Yf = U_ROUND(Coords->Y)( (Coords->Y) > 0 ? floor((Coords->Y)+0.5) : ( (Coords
->Y) < 0 ? -floor(-(Coords->Y)+0.5) : (Coords->Y)
) );
3090
3091 /* this is not a very efficient method, too much mucking around with memory */
3092
3093 poi = U_PMF_INTEGER7_set(X);
3094 if(!poi)poi = U_PMF_INTEGER15_set(X); /* This one must work because of the range checking, above */
3095 po = U_PO_append(po, poi->Data, poi->Used);
3096 U_PO_free(&poi);
3097 if(!po)goto end;
3098
3099 poi = U_PMF_INTEGER7_set(Y);
3100 if(!poi)poi = U_PMF_INTEGER15_set(Y); /* This one must work because of the range checking, above */
3101 po = U_PO_append(po, poi->Data, poi->Used);
3102 U_PO_free(&poi);
3103 if(!po)goto end;
3104 }
3105 /* Because the values stored were some unpredictable combination of 1 and 2 bytes, the last byte may not end
3106 on a 4 byte boundary. Make it do so by padding with up to 3 zero bytes. */
3107
3108 int residual;
3109 residual = 3 & po->Used;
3110 if(residual){
3111 po = U_PO_append(po, NULL((void*)0), (4 - residual));
3112 if(!po)goto end;
3113 }
3114
3115end:
3116 if(!po)U_PO_free(&holdpo);
3117 return(holdpo);
3118}

3160 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error. PseudoObject contains Elements followed by the array of U_PMF_RECT objects.
3161 \param Elements Number of elements in Rects
3162 \param Rects Array of U_PMF_RECT structures
3163
3164 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.38, Microsoft name: EmfPlusRect Object
3165*/
3166U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMF_RECTN_set(uint32_t Elements, U_PMF_RECT *Rects){
3167 if(!Rects){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3168 uint32_t count = Elements;
3169 U_SERIAL_DESC *List = (U_SERIAL_DESC *) malloc((Elements + 2) * sizeof(U_SERIAL_DESC));
3170 U_SERIAL_DESC *Lptr = List;
3171 if(!List){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3172 *Lptr++ = (U_SERIAL_DESC){&Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1};
3173 for(; count; count--, Lptr++, Rects++){
3174 *Lptr = (U_SERIAL_DESC){Rects, 2, 4, U_LE1};
3175 }
3176 *Lptr = (U_SERIAL_DESC){NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF};
3177 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMF_RECT_OID0x02020238 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000, List);
3178 free(List);
3179 return(po);
3180}

3244/**
3245 \brief Create and set a U_PMF_REGIONNODE PseudoObject
3246 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
3247 \param Type RegionNodeDataType Enumeration
3248 \param Rnd (optional) U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_REGIONNODEPATH, U_PMF_RECTF, or U_PMF_REGIONNODECHILDNODES object (Region Node Data)
3249
3250
3251 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.40, Microsoft name: EmfPlusRegionNode Object
3252*/
3253U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMF_REGIONNODE_set(int32_t Type, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rnd){
3254 int32_t pType;
3255 /* make sure that the type of Rnd agrees with Type */
3256 if(Rnd){
3257 pType = U_OID_To_RNDT(Rnd->Type);
3258 if( pType < 0){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3259 if((pType > 0) && (pType != Type)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3260 if((pType == 0) &&
3261 (
3262 (Type < U_RNDT_And0x00000001) ||
3263 (Type > U_RNDT_Complement0x00000005)
3264 )
3265 ){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3266 if((Type == U_RNDT_Rect0x10000000) && (Rnd->Type != U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3267 if((Type == U_RNDT_Path0x10000001) && (Rnd->Type != U_PMF_REGIONNODEPATH_OID0x02020242)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3268
3269 }
3270 else { /* only U_RNDT_Empty and U_RNDT_Infinite do not have data */
3271 if((Type != U_RNDT_Empty0x10000002) ||
3272 (Type != U_RNDT_Infinite0x10000003) ){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3273 }
3274
3275
3276 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3277 {&Type, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3278 {(Rnd ? Rnd->Data : NULL((void*)0)), (Rnd ? Rnd->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
3279 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3280 };
3281 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMF_REGIONNODE_OID0x02020240, List);
3282 return(po);
3283}

3671//! \cond
3672/* internal routine, not part of the API.
3673 Returns a PseudoObject containing a U_PMR_CMN_HDR_OID object.
3674 The type is something like U_PMR_OFFSETCLIP (the record type, NOT the U_PMR_OFFSETCLIP_OID PseudoObject Type!).
3675 The U_PMR_RECFLAG bit is added both in the data and in the Type of the PseudoObject.
3676 If that bit is already set no harm, no foul.
3677*/
3678
3679U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(uint32_t Type, uint16_t Flags, uint32_t DataSize){
3680
3681 uint32_t Size = 12 + UP4(DataSize)(4 * ((DataSize + 3 ) / 4)); /* The header itself is always 12, PMR records must be a multiple of 4 */
3682 Type |= U_PMR_RECFLAG0x4000;
3683 uint16_t utmp16 = Type;
3684 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3685 {&utmp16, 2, 1, U_LE1},
3686 {&Flags, 2, 1, U_LE1}, /* Microsoft EMF+ manual is BE, but this field in this implementation is LE */
3687 {&Size, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3688 {&DataSize, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3689 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3690 };
3691 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_CMN_HDR_OID0x40000000, List);
3692 return(po);
3693}
3694//! \endcond

3786/**
3787 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_SETCLIPRECT PseudoObject
3788 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
3789 \param CMenum CombineMode enumeration..
3790 \param Rect U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing an U_PMF_RECTF object or an array of U_PMF_RECTF objects (the first is used)
3791
3792
3793 EMF+ manual 2.3.1.4, Microsoft name: EmfPlusSetClipRect Record, Index 0x32
3794*/
3795U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_SETCLIPRECT_set(uint32_t CMenum, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rect){
3796 int Size=4*4;
3797 const char *start;
3798 uint16_t utmp16 = ((CMenum & U_FF_MASK_CM40x000F) << U_FF_SHFT_CM40x0008);
3799 if(Rect){
3800 if( Rect->Type == U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239){
3801 start = Rect->Data;
3802 }
3803 else if(Rect->Type == (U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){
3804 start = Rect->Data + 4;
3805 }
3806 else { return(0); }
3807 }
3808 else { return(0); }
3809
3810 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_SETCLIPRECT0x0032,utmp16,Size);
3811 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3812 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3813 {start, 4, 4, U_XE0},
3814 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3815 };
3816 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_SETCLIPRECT_OID0x02030104, List);
3817 U_PO_free(&ph);
3818 return(po);
3819}

3851

3853*/
3854U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_COMMENT_set(size_t cbData, const void *Data){
3855 if(UP4(cbData)(4 * ((cbData + 3 ) / 4)) != cbData){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }

3858
3859 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_COMMENT0x0003,0,Size);
3860 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3861 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3862 {Data, cbData, 1, U_XE0},
3863 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3864 };
3865 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_COMMENT_OID0x02030201, List);
3866 U_PO_free(&ph);
3867 return(po);
3868}

3908/**
3909 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_HEADER PseudoObject
3910 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
3911 \param IsDual set = Dual-mode file, clear= EMF+ only file.
3912 \param IsVideo set = video device, clear= printer. Ignore all other bits.
3913 \param Version U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_GRAPHICSVERSION object
3914 \param LogicalDpiX Horizontal resolution reference device in DPI
3915 \param LogicalDpiY Vertical resolution reference device in DPI
3916
3917
3918 EMF+ manual 2.3.3.3, Microsoft name: EmfPlusHeader Record, Index 0x01
3919*/
3920U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_HEADER_set(int IsDual, int IsVideo, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Version,
3921 uint32_t LogicalDpiX, uint32_t LogicalDpiY){
3922 if(!Version || (Version->Type != U_PMF_GRAPHICSVERSION_OID0x02020219)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3923 int Size=Version->Used + 3*4;
3924 uint16_t utmp16 = (IsDual ? U_PPF_DM0x0001 : 0);
3925 uint32_t Flags = (IsVideo ? U_PPF_VIDEO0x0001 : 0);
3926 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_HEADER0x0001,utmp16,Size);
3927 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3928 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3929 {Version->Data, Version->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3930 {&Flags, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3931 {&LogicalDpiX, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3932 {&LogicalDpiY, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3933 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3934 };
3935 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_HEADER_OID0x02030303, List);
3936 U_PO_free(&ph);
3937 return(po);
3938}

3965/**
3966 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWARC PseudoObject
3967 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
3968 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
3969 \param Start Start angle, >=0.0, degrees clockwise from 3:00
3970 \param Sweep Sweep angle, -360<= angle <=360, degrees clockwise from Start
3971 \param Rect U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_RECT or U_PMF_RECTF object
3972
3973
3974 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.2, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawArc Record, Index 0x12
3975*/
3976U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWARC_set(uint32_t PenID, U_FLOAT Start, U_FLOAT Sweep, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rect){
3977 int ctype;
3978 if(PenID>63)return(NULL((void*)0));
3979 if(!Rect){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3980 else {
3981 if( Rect->Type == U_PMF_RECT_OID0x02020238 ){ ctype = 1; }
3982 else if(Rect->Type == U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239){ ctype = 0; }
3983 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
3984 }
3985 int Size = 2*4 + Rect->Used;
3986 uint16_t utmp16 = (ctype ? U_PPF_C0x4000 : 0) | (PenID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
3987 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWARC0x0012,utmp16,Size);
3988 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
3989 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3990 {&Start, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3991 {&Sweep, 4, 1, U_LE1},
3992 {Rect->Data, Rect->Used, 1, U_XE0},
3993 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
3994 };
3995 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWARC_OID0x02030402, List);
3996 U_PO_free(&ph);
3997 return(po);
3998}
3999
4000/**
4001 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS PseudoObject
4002 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4003 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4004 \param Points U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing first Elements, then a U_PMF_POINT, U_PMF_POINTR or U_PMF_POINTF object
4005
4006
4007 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.3, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawBeziers Record, Index 0x19
4008*/
4009U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS_set(uint32_t PenID, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Points){
4010 int ctype, RelAbs;
4011 if(PenID>63)return(NULL((void*)0));
4012 if(Points){
4013 if( Points->Type == U_PMF_POINTR_OID0x02020237){ RelAbs = 1; ctype = 0; }
4014 else if(Points->Type == (U_PMF_POINT_OID0x02020235 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ RelAbs = 0; ctype = 1; }
4015 else if(Points->Type == (U_PMF_POINTF_OID0x02020236 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ RelAbs = 0; ctype = 0; }
4016 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4017 }
4018 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4019 int Size = Points->Used;
4020 uint16_t utmp16 = (ctype ? U_PPF_C0x4000 : 0) | (RelAbs ? U_PPF_P0x0800 : 0) |(PenID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4021 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS0x0019,utmp16,Size);
4022 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4023 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4024 {Points->Data, Points->Used, 1, U_XE0}, /* Includes Elements */
4025 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4026 };
4027 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS_OID0x02030403, List);

4069 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}

4076/**
4077 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWCURVE PseudoObject
4078 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4079 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4080 \param Tension Controls splines, 0 is straight line, >0 is curved
4081 \param Offset The starting point in the list of points, 0 is first.
4082 \param NSegs Number of segments to draw. Starting at Offset go NSegs straight lines, must not run out of points..
4083 \param Points U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing an element count then a series of U_PMF_POINT or U_PMF_POINTF object
4084
4085
4086 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.5, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawCurve Record, Index 0x18
4087
4088 Curve is a cardinal spline, using doubled terminator points to generate curves for the terminal segments.
4089
4090 References sent by MS support:
4091
4092 http://alvyray.com/Memos/CG/Pixar/spline77.pdf
4093
4094 http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/4cf6we5y(v=vs.110).aspx
4095
4096*/
4097U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWCURVE_set(uint32_t PenID, U_FLOAT Tension, uint32_t Offset, uint32_t NSegs, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Points){
4098 int ctype;
4099 if(PenID>63)return(NULL((void*)0));
4100 if(!Points){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4101 if(!NSegs){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4102 else {
4103 if( Points->Type == (U_PMF_POINT_OID0x02020235 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ ctype = 1; }
4104 else if(Points->Type == (U_PMF_POINTF_OID0x02020236 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ ctype = 0; }
4105 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4106 }
4107 uint32_t Elements = (Points->Used - 4)/(ctype ? 4 : 8); /* This way do not need to worry about byte order */
4108 if(Offset + NSegs + 1 > Elements){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4109 int Size = 3*4 + Points->Used;
4110 uint16_t utmp16 = (ctype ? U_PPF_C0x4000 : 0) |(PenID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4111 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWCURVE0x0018,utmp16,Size);
4112 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4113 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4114 {&Tension, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4115 {&Offset, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4116 {&NSegs, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4117 {Points->Data, Points->Used, 1, U_XE0}, /* Elements, points */
4118 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4119 };
4120 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWCURVE_OID0x02030405, List);
4121 U_PO_free(&ph);
4122 return(po);
4123}

4125/**
4126 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING PseudoObject
4127 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4128 \param FontID U_PMF_FONT object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4129 \param BrushID U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_ARGB or a U_PMF_4NUM. Color or U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4130 \param DSOFlags DriverStringOptions flags
4131 \param HasMatrix If 1 record contains a TransformMatrix field, if 0 it does not.
4132 \param GlyphCount The number of Elements in Glyphs, must agree with the number of elements in Points.
4133 \param Glyphs If U_DSO_CmapLookup is set in DSOFlags this is an array of UTF16LE characters, otherwise, it is an array of indices into the U_PMF_FONT object indexed by Object_ID in flags.
4134 \param Points U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_POINTF object
4135 \param Tm U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX object. Apply to Glyphs & Positions. Present if HasMatrix is 1
4136
4137
4138 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.6, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawDriverString Record, Index 0x36
4139*/
4140U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING_set(uint32_t FontID, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *BrushID,
4141 uint32_t DSOFlags, uint32_t HasMatrix, uint32_t GlyphCount,
4142 const uint16_t *Glyphs, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Points, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Tm){
4143 int btype;
4144 if(FontID>63){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4145 if(!Glyphs){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4146 if(!Points || (Points->Type != (U_PMF_POINTF_OID0x02020236 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000))){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4147 uint32_t Elements = (Points->Used -4)/4;
4148 if(GlyphCount != Elements){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4149 if(BrushID){
4150 if( BrushID->Used != 4){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4151 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_ARGB_OID0x02020201){ btype = 1; }
4152 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_4NUM_OID0x40000001){ btype = 0; }
4153 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4154 }
4155 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4156 int Size = 4 + BrushID->Used + 3*4 + Elements*2 + (Points->Used - 4);
4157 if(HasMatrix){
4158 if(!Tm){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4159 else if(Tm->Type != (U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX_OID0x02020247)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4160 Size += Tm->Used;
4161 }
4162 uint16_t utmp16 = (btype ? U_PPF_B0x8000 : 0) |(FontID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4163 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING0x0036,utmp16,Size);
4164 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4165 {ph->Data,ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4166 {BrushID->Data, BrushID->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4167 {&DSOFlags, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4168 {&HasMatrix, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4169 {&Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4170 {Glyphs, 2, Elements, U_LE1},
4171 {Points->Data + 4, Points->Used - 4, 1, U_XE0}, /* omit Elements */
4172 {(HasMatrix ? Tm->Data : NULL((void*)0)), (HasMatrix ? Tm->Used : 0), 1, U_XE0},
4173 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4174 };
4175 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING_OID0x02030406, List);
4176 U_PO_free(&ph);
4177 return(po);
4178}

4390/**
4391 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWRECTS PseudoObject
4392 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4393 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4394 \param Rects U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing 1 rect OR a count N follwed by N rects. Rects may be either U_PMF_RECT or U_PMF_RECTF
4395
4396
4397 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.13, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawRects Record, Index 0x0B
4398*/
4399U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWRECTS_set(uint32_t PenID, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rects){
4400 int ctype;
4401 int just1;
4402 uint32_t Elements=1; /* only used when a single rect is passed in, not an array, not even an array with one member*/
4403 if(PenID>63){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4404 if(Rects){
4405 if( (Rects->Type & U_PMF_MASK_OID0x7FFFFFFF) == U_PMF_RECT_OID0x02020238 ){ ctype = 1; }
4406 else if( (Rects->Type & U_PMF_MASK_OID0x7FFFFFFF) == U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239){ ctype = 0; }
4407 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4408 }
4409 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4410 just1 = (Rects->Type & U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000 ? 0 : 1);
4411 int Size = Rects->Used + (just1 ? 4 : 0); /* Elements in Rects for array, not for single */
4412 uint16_t utmp16 = (ctype ? U_PPF_C0x4000 : 0)| (PenID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4413 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWRECTS0x000B,utmp16,Size);
4414 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4415 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4416 {(just1 ? (char *)&Elements : NULL((void*)0)), (just1 ? 4: 0), 1, U_LE1}, /* element count if a single Rect was passed in, empty otherwise */
4417 {Rects->Data, Rects->Used, 1, U_XE0}, /* Elements + Array, already stored in Rects, if an array was passed in, just rect if a single */
4418 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4419 };
4420 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWRECTS_OID0x02030413, List);
4421 U_PO_free(&ph);
4422 return(po);
4423}

4425/**
4426 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_DRAWSTRING PseudoObject
4427 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4428 \param FontID U_PMF_FONT object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4429 \param BrushID U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_ARGB or a U_PMF_4NUM. Color or U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4430 \param FormatID U_PMF_STRINGFORMAT object in EMF+ Object Table.
4431 \param Length Number of characters in the string.
4432 \param Rect U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_RECTF object, string's bounding box
4433 \param Text Array of UFT-16LE unicode characters.
4434
4435
4436 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.14, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawString Record, Index 0x1C
4437*/
4438U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_DRAWSTRING_set(uint32_t FontID, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *BrushID,
4439 uint32_t FormatID, uint32_t Length, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rect, const uint16_t *Text){
4440 int btype;
4441 if(FontID>63){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4442 if(!Length){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4443 else if (!Text){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4444 if(!Rect || Rect->Type != U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4445 if(BrushID){
4446 if( BrushID->Used != 4){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4447 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_ARGB_OID0x02020201){ btype = 1; }
4448 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_4NUM_OID0x40000001){ btype = 0; }
4449 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4450 }
4451 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4452 int Size = BrushID->Used + 2*4 + Rect->Used +2*Length;
4453 uint16_t utmp16 = (btype ? U_PPF_B0x8000 : 0)| (FontID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4454 uint32_t pad = (0x1 & Length ? 2 : 0);
4455 Size+=pad;
4456 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_DRAWSTRING0x001C,utmp16,Size);
4457 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4458 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4459 {BrushID->Data, BrushID->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4460 {&FormatID, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4461 {&Length, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4462 {Rect->Data, Rect->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4463 {Text, 2*Length, 1, U_XE0},
4464 {NULL((void*)0), pad, (pad ? 1 : 0), (pad ? U_XE0 : U_XX0xFF)}, /* Entire record must be a multiple of 4 */
4465 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4466 };
4467 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_DRAWSTRING_OID0x02030414, List);
4468 U_PO_free(&ph);
4469 return(po);
4470}

4668 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_FILLRECTS PseudoObject

4670 \param BrushID U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_ARGB or a U_PMF_4NUM. Color or U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4671 \param Rects U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing 1 rect OR a count N followed by N rects. Rects may be either U_PMF_RECT or U_PMF_RECTF
4672
4673
4674 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.20, Microsoft name: EmfPlusFillRects Record, Index 0x0A
4675*/
4676U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_FILLRECTS_set(const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *BrushID, const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rects){
4677 int btype, ctype;
4678 int just1;
4679 uint32_t Elements=1; /* only used when a single rect is passed in, not an array, not even an array with one member*/
4680 if(BrushID){
4681 if( BrushID->Used != 4){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4682 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_ARGB_OID0x02020201){ btype = 1; }
4683 else if( BrushID->Type == U_PMF_4NUM_OID0x40000001){ btype = 0; }
4684 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4685 }
4686 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4687 if(Rects){
4688 if( (Rects->Type & U_PMF_MASK_OID0x7FFFFFFF) == U_PMF_RECT_OID0x02020238 ){ ctype = 1; }
4689 else if( (Rects->Type & U_PMF_MASK_OID0x7FFFFFFF) == U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239){ ctype = 0; }
4690 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }

4694 int Size = BrushID->Used + Rects->Used + (just1 ? 4 : 0); /* Elements in Rects for array, not for single */
4695 uint16_t utmp16 = (btype ? U_PPF_B0x8000 : 0)|(ctype ? U_PPF_C0x4000 : 0);
4696 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_FILLRECTS0x000A,utmp16,Size);
4697 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4698 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4699 {BrushID->Data, BrushID->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4700 {(just1 ? (char *)&Elements : NULL((void*)0)), (just1 ? 4: 0), 1, U_LE1}, /* element count if a single Rect was passed in, empty otherwise */
4701 {Rects->Data, Rects->Used, 1, U_XE0}, /* Elements + Array, already stored in Rects, if an array was passed in, just rect if a single */
4702 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4703 };
4704 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_FILLRECTS_OID0x02030420, List);
4705 U_PO_free(&ph);

4740/**
4741 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_OBJECT PseudoObject from another PseudoObject
4742 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4743 \param ObjID Index for this object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4744 \param Po U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing an object type that may be stored in the EMF+ object table
4745*/
4746U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_OBJECT_PO_set(uint32_t ObjID, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Po){
4747 if(!Po){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4748 int otype = U_OID_To_OT(Po->Type); /* This will return 0 if the type is not valid for an object */
4749 if(!otype){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4750 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMR_OBJECT_set(ObjID, otype, 0, 0, Po->Used, Po->Data); /* 0,0 = rec. not continued, TSize value (ignored) */
4751 return(po);
4752}
4753
4754/**
4755 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_OBJECT PseudoObject
4756 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4757 \param ObjID Index for this object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
4758 \param otype ObjectType enumeration for this Object
4759 \param ntype Set: object definition continues in next record; Clear: this is the sole object definition record
4760 \param TSize If ntype is set the total number of data bytes split across multiple records. If ntype is clear, it is ignored.
4761 \param cbData Object's data size, in bytes.
4762 \param Data Object's data. Type from otype.
4763
4764
4765 EMF+ manual 2.3.5.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusObject Record, Index 0x13
4766
4767 Normally this is only called by U_PMR_OBJECT_PO_set().
4768
4769 U_PMR_OBJECT records can only hold a maximum of 65020 bytes of data. If the object is larger than that
4770 then multiple U_PMR_OBJECT records are created, one after the other. If this
4771 happens each record has cbData following ph, and the ntype flag is set. If all of the data is less than 65020
4772 then cbData is NOT entered following ph, and the ntype flag is clear.
4773
4774 Call initially in all cases with ntype clear and TSize = 0. If the record needs to be fragmented
4775 the function will call itself recursively to do so.
4776
4777*/
4778U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_OBJECT_set(uint32_t ObjID, int otype, int ntype, uint32_t TSize, size_t cbData, const char *Data){
4779 uint32_t CSize;
4780 int Pad = UP4(TSize)(4 * ((TSize + 3 ) / 4)) - TSize;
4781 if((otype < U_OT_Brush0x01) || (otype > U_OT_CustomLineCap0x09)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4782 if(ntype && (cbData > U_OBJRECLIM65020)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4783 if(!Data || !cbData){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4784 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po;
4785
4786 if(!ntype && !TSize && (cbData > U_OBJRECLIM65020)){
4787 ntype = 1;
4788 TSize = cbData;
4789 po = U_PO_create(NULL((void*)0), TSize + 16 * (1 + (TSize/cbData)), 0, U_PMR_OBJECT_OID0x02030501);
4790 if(po){
4791 while(cbData){
4792 CSize = (cbData > U_OBJRECLIM65020 ? U_OBJRECLIM65020 : cbData);
4793 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *pot = U_PMR_OBJECT_set(ObjID, otype, ntype, TSize, CSize, Data);
4794 if(!pot)break;
4795 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *newpo = U_PO_po_append(po, pot, U_PMF_KEEP_ELEMENTS0);
4796 U_PO_free(&pot);
4797 if(!newpo)break;
4798 po = newpo;
4799 Data += U_OBJRECLIM65020;
4800 cbData -= CSize;
4801 }
4802 if(cbData){ /* some error */
4803 U_PO_free(&po);
4804 }
4805 }
4806 }
4807 else {
4808 /* Send in DataSize, U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set will adjust Header Size with 1-3 pad bytes if needed */
4809 uint16_t utmp16 = otype << 8 | (ntype ? U_PPF_N0x8000 : 0) | (ObjID & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000;
4810 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_OBJECT0x0008,utmp16,cbData + (ntype ? 4 : 0));
4811 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4812 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0 },
4813 {(ntype ? &TSize : NULL((void*)0)), (ntype ? 4 : 0), (ntype ? 1 : 0), U_LE1 },
4814 {Data, cbData, 1, U_XE0 },
4815 {NULL((void*)0), (Pad ? Pad : 0), (Pad ? 1 : 0), (Pad ? U_XE0 : U_XX0xFF)}, /* Either 1-3 pad bytes or a terminator */
4816 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF} /* terminator, possibly a second in the list, which is harmless */
4817 };
4818 po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_OBJECT_OID0x02030501, List);
4819 U_PO_free(&ph);
4820 }
4821 return(po);
4822}
4823
4824/**
4825 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_SERIALIZABLEOBJECT PseudoObject
4826 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
4827 \param Siepb U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a "Serialized image effects parameter block". One of the ImageEffects objects.
4828
4829 EMF+ manual 2.3.5.2, Microsoft name: EmfPlusSerializableObject Record, Index 0x38
4830
4831
4832 This sets an ImageEffect in the renderer, which will be applied to the next EmfPlusDrawImagePoints
4833 record that is encountered. The image effect is "consumed" by that EmfPlusDrawImagePoints record, resetting
4834 the renderer to its original state.\n
4835
4836 WARNING! Windows XP Preview does not show filter effects, whether or not U_PPF_E is set. They are visible if the EMF+
4837 file is inserted as an image into PowerPoint.
4838
4839*/
4840U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_SERIALIZABLEOBJECT_set(const U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Siepb){
4841 if(!Siepb){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4842 uint8_t *GUID = U_OID_To_GUID(Siepb->Type);
4843 if(!GUID){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
4844 /* PO Used is size_t, might be 8 bytes, value in record must be 4 bytes */
4845 uint32_t Used = Siepb->Used;
4846 int Size = 16 + 4 + Siepb->Used;
4847 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_SERIALIZABLEOBJECT0x0038,0,Size);
4848 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
4849 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4850 {GUID, 16, 1, U_XE0},
4851 {&Used, 4, 1, U_LE1},
4852 {Siepb->Data, Siepb->Used, 1, U_XE0},
4853 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
4854 };
4855 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_SERIALIZABLEOBJECT_OID0x02030502, List);
4856 U_PO_free(&ph);
4857 free(GUID);
4858 return(po);
4859}

5034 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_BEGINCONTAINER PseudoObject
5035 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
5036 \param UTenum UnitType enumeration
5037 \param DstRect a U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_RECTF object. with SrcRect specifies a transformation
5038 \param SrcRect a U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_RECTF object. with DstRect specifies a transformation
5039 \param StackID EMF+ Object Stack Index to use for this graphics container
5040
5041
5042 EMF+ manual 2.3.7.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusBeginContainer Record, Index 0x27
5043*/
5044U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_BEGINCONTAINER_set(int UTenum, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *DstRect, U_PSEUDO_OBJ *SrcRect, uint32_t StackID){
5045 if(UTenum < U_UT_World0x00 || UTenum > U_UT_Millimeter0x06){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
5046 if(!DstRect || (DstRect->Type != U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
5047 if(!SrcRect || (SrcRect->Type != U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239)){ return(NULL((void*)0)); }
5048 int Size = DstRect->Used + SrcRect->Used + 4;
5049 uint16_t utmp16 = (UTenum & U_FF_MASK_UT0x00FF) << U_FF_SHFT_UT0x0008;
5050 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_BEGINCONTAINER0x0027,utmp16,Size);
5051 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
5052 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
5053 {DstRect->Data, DstRect->Used, 1, U_XE0},
5054 {SrcRect->Data, SrcRect->Used, 1, U_XE0},
5055 {&StackID, 4, 1, U_LE1},
5056 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
5057 };
5058 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_BEGINCONTAINER_OID0x02030701, List);
5059 U_PO_free(&ph);
5060 return(po);
5061}

5151/**
5152 \brief Create and set a U_PMR_SETTSCLIP PseudoObject
5153 \return Pointer to PseudoObject, NULL on error
5154 \param Rects a U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing an array of U_PMF_RECT or U_PMF_RECTF objects.
5155
5156
5157 EMF+ manual 2.3.8.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusSetTSClip Record, Index 0x3A
5158*/
5159U_PSEUDO_OBJ *U_PMR_SETTSCLIP_set(U_PSEUDO_OBJ *Rects){
5160 int ctype;
5161 uint32_t Elements;
5162 if(Rects){
5163 if( Rects->Type == (U_PMF_RECT_OID0x02020238 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ ctype = 1; Elements = (Rects->Used - 4)/8; }
5164 else if(Rects->Type == (U_PMF_RECTF_OID0x02020239 | U_PMF_ARRAY_OID0x80000000)){ ctype = 0; Elements = (Rects->Used - 4)/16; }
5165 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
5166 }
5167 else { return(NULL((void*)0)); }
5168 int Size = Rects->Used; /* Rects includes Elements */
5169 uint16_t utmp16 = (ctype ? U_PPF_K0x8000 : 0) | (Elements & U_FF_MASK_TSC0x7FFF) << U_FF_SHFT_TSC0x0000;
5170 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *ph = U_PMR_CMN_HDR_set(U_PMR_SETTSCLIP0x003A,utmp16,Size);
5171 const U_SERIAL_DESC List[] = {
5172 {ph->Data, ph->Used, 1, U_XE0},
5173 {Rects->Data, Rects->Used, 1, U_XE0},
5174 {NULL((void*)0),0,0,U_XX0xFF}
5175 };
5176 U_PSEUDO_OBJ *po = U_PMF_SERIAL_set(U_PMR_SETTSCLIP_OID0x02030801, List);
5177 U_PO_free(&ph);
5178 return(po);
5179}

5216/**

5219 \param xmtype Set: Post multiply; Clear: Pre multiply
5220 \param Tm a U_PSEUDO_OBJ containing a U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX. (Transformation matrix)
5221
5222
5223 EMF+ manual 2.3.9.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusMultiplyWorldTransform Record, Index 0x2C
5224*/

5384/*
5385
5386 end of U_PMF_*_set() functions
5387 =====================================================================================
5388 start of U_PMF_*_get() functions
5389
5390 These functions all take a blimit value so that they can check if the data description in the fields
5391 they process extend beyond the end of the record.
5392
5393*/

5395
5396//! \cond
5397/* core _get functions, not accessed outside of this routine */
5398
5399/* get copies of up to 0-6 consecutive 4 byte values and a pointer to the rest */
5400int U_PMF_CORE1_get(const char *contents, void *v1, void *v2, void *v3, void *v4, void *v5, void *v6, const char **vR){
5401 if(v1){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v1, &contents, 4);
5402 if(v2){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v2, &contents, 4);
5403 if(v3){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v3, &contents, 4);
5404 if(v4){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v4, &contents, 4);
5405 if(v5){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v5, &contents, 4);
5406 if(v6){ U_PMF_MEMCPY_SRCSHIFT(v6, &contents, 4); }}}}}}
5407 if(vR){ *vR = contents; }
5408 return(1);
5409}
5410//! \endcond

5413/**
5414 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_BRUSH object
5415 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
5416 \param contents Record from which to extract data
5417 \param Version EmfPlusGraphicsVersion object
5418 \param Type BrushType Enumeration
5419 \param Data one of the 5 types of Brush data
5420 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
5421
5422 EMF+ manual 2.2.1.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusBrush Object
5423
5424 Caller must check Data for possible memory access violations.
5425*/
5426int U_PMF_BRUSH_get(const char *contents, uint32_t *Version, uint32_t *Type, const char **Data, const char *blimit){
5427 if(!contents || !Version || !Type || !Data || !blimit){ return(0); }
5428 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents,sizeof(U_PMF_BRUSH), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_BRUSH)) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeof
(U_PMF_BRUSH)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t
*)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >=
(int)(sizeof(U_PMF_BRUSH)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5429 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Version, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5430 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Type, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5431 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Data, &contents, 0);
5432 return(1);
5433}

5457/**
5458 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_FONT object
5459 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
5460 \param contents Record from which to extract data
5461 \param Version EmfPlusGraphicsVersion object
5462 \param EmSize em size in units of SizeUnit
5463 \param SizeUnit UnitType enumeration
5464 \param FSFlags FontStyle flags
5465 \param Length Number of Unicode Characters in FamilyName
5466 \param Data Unicode (UTF-16LE) name of font family
5467
5468 EMF+ manual 2.2.1.3, Microsoft name: EmfPlusFont Object
5469
5470 Caller must check Data for possible memory access violations.
5471*/
5472int U_PMF_FONT_get(const char *contents, uint32_t *Version, U_FLOAT *EmSize, uint32_t *SizeUnit,
5473 int32_t *FSFlags, uint32_t *Length, const char **Data, const char *blimit){
5474 if(!contents || !Version || !EmSize || !SizeUnit || !FSFlags || !Length || !Data || !blimit){ return(0); }
5475 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_FONT), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_FONT)) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeof
(U_PMF_FONT)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t
*)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >=
(int)(sizeof(U_PMF_FONT)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5476 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Version, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5477 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, EmSize, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5478 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, SizeUnit, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5479 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, FSFlags, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5480 contents += 4; /* Reserved field, which is ignored */
5481 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Length, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5482 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Data, &contents, 0);
5483 return(1);
5484}

5518*/
5519int U_PMF_IMAGEATTRIBUTES_get(const char *contents, uint32_t *Version, uint32_t *WrapMode, uint32_t *ClampColor,
5520 uint32_t *ObjectClamp, const char *blimit){
5521 if(!contents || !Version || !WrapMode || !ClampColor || !ObjectClamp || !blimit){ return(0); }
5522 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_IMAGEATTRIBUTES), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_IMAGEATTRIBUTES)) < sizeof(int) || (
int)(sizeof(U_PMF_IMAGEATTRIBUTES)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)
(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) -
(int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_IMAGEATTRIBUTES
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

5532/**
5533 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_PATH object
5534 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
5535 \param contents Record from which to extract data
5536 \param Version EmfPlusGraphicsVersion object
5537 \param Count Number of points and point types in this object
5538 \param Flags PathPoint Flags
5539 \param Points array of points type PMFPointR, PMFPoint, or PMFPointF
5540 \param Types array of U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPERLE and/or U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPE
5541
5542 EMF+ manual 2.2.1.6, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPath Object
5543
5544 Caller must check Types for possible memory access violations if type can be U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPERLE.
5545*/
5546int U_PMF_PATH_get(const char *contents, uint32_t *Version, uint32_t *Count, uint16_t *Flags,
5547 const char **Points, const char **Types, const char *blimit){
5548 if(!contents || !Version || !Count || !Flags || !Points || !Types || !blimit){ return(0); }
5549 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_PATH), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_PATH)) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeof
(U_PMF_PATH)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t
*)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >=
(int)(sizeof(U_PMF_PATH)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5550 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Version, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5551 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Count, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5552 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Flags, 2, 1, U_LE1);
5553 contents+=2; /* reserved */
5554 uint32_t sizeP, sizeT;
5555 if(*Flags & U_PPF_P0x0800){
5556 sizeP = U_PMF_LEN_REL715(contents,*Count); //DEBUG
5557 printf("DEBUG U_PMF_PATH_get count:%d LENREL715:%d\n",*Count,sizeP);fflush(stdoutstdout);
5558 }
5559 else if(*Flags & U_PPF_C0x4000){ sizeP = *Count * sizeof(U_PMF_POINT); }
5560 else { sizeP = *Count * sizeof(U_PMF_POINTF); }
5561 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeP, blimit)( (sizeof(sizeP) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeP) < 0) ? 1
: ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeP) ? 0 : 1
))))return(0);
5562 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Points, &contents, 0);
5563 contents += sizeP;
5564 /* this limit is correct if there are only U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPE PointTypes, it is a lower bound if
5565 there can also be U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPERLE */
5566 sizeT = *Count * sizeof(U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPE);
5567 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeT, blimit)( (sizeof(sizeT) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeT) < 0) ? 1
: ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeT) ? 0 : 1
))))return(0);
5568 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Types, &contents, 0);
5569 return(1);
5570}
5571

5573 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_PEN object
5574 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
5575 \param contents Record from which to extract data

5578 \param PenData Pen description
5579 \param Brush Brush Description

5586 if(!contents || !Type || !PenData || !Brush || !blimit){ return(0); }
5587 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_PEN), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_PEN)) < sizeof(int) || (int)(sizeof
(U_PMF_PEN)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t
*)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >=
(int)(sizeof(U_PMF_PEN)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5588 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Version, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5589 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Type, 4, 1, U_LE1);

5591 *Brush = *PenData + U_PMF_LEN_PENDATA(*PenData);

5884/**
5885 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_CUSTOMLINECAPOPTIONALDATA object
5886 \return on success 3,5, or 7 (for varying combinations of data present) or 1 (no data is present), 0 on error
5887 \param contents Record from which to extract data
5888 \param Flags bits set to indicate the presence of FillData and/or LineData
5889 \param FillData Path to fill (optional)
5890 \param LineData Path to stroke (optional)
5891
5892 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.14, Microsoft name: EmfPlusCustomLineCapOptionalData Object
5893
5894 Caller must check LineData for possible memory access violations.
5895*/
5896int U_PMF_CUSTOMLINECAPOPTIONALDATA_get(const char *contents, uint32_t Flags, const char **FillData, const char **LineData, const char *blimit){
5897 uint32_t length;
5898 int status = 1;
5899 if(!contents || !*FillData || !*LineData || !blimit){ return(0); }
5900 /* this structure is entirely optional */
5901 if(Flags & U_CLCD_FillPath0x01){
5902 if(!FillData){ return(0); }
5903 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, 4, blimit)( (sizeof(4) < sizeof(int) || (int)(4) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(4) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5904 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &length, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5905 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, length, blimit)( (sizeof(length) < sizeof(int) || (int)(length) < 0) ?
1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(length) ? 0 : 1
))))return(0);
5906 contents -= 4; /* undo the unneeded shift from preceding */
5907 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(FillData, &contents, 4 + length);
5908 status += 2;
5909 }
5910 else { *FillData = NULL((void*)0); }
5911
5912 if(Flags & U_CLCD_LinePath0x02){
5913 if(!LineData){ return(0); }
5914 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, 4, blimit)( (sizeof(4) < sizeof(int) || (int)(4) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(4) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
5915 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &length, 4, 1, U_LE1);
5916 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, length, blimit)( (sizeof(length) < sizeof(int) || (int)(length) < 0) ?
1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(length) ? 0 : 1
))))return(0);
5917 contents -= 4; /* undo the unneeded shift from preceding */
5918 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(LineData, &contents, 0);
5919 status += 4;
5920 }
5921 else { *LineData = NULL((void*)0); }
5922 return(status);
5923}

) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t
*)(contents) >= (int)(*Elements * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) ? 0 : 1
))))return(0);
5958 *Lengths = (U_FLOAT *)malloc(*Elements * sizeof(U_FLOAT));
5959 if(!*Lengths){ return(0); }
5960 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, *Lengths, 4, *Elements, U_LE1);
5961 return(1);
5962}

6011*/
6012int U_PMF_GRAPHICSVERSION_get(const char *contents, int *Signature, int *GrfVersion, const char *blimit){

(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) -

)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

6041/**
6042 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_INTEGER7 object
6043 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6044 \param contents Record from which to extract data
6045 \param Value 7 bit signed integer (stored in an integer)
6046 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6047
6048 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.21, Microsoft name: EmfPlusInteger7 Object
6049*/
6050int U_PMF_INTEGER7_get(const char **contents, U_FLOAT *Value, const char *blimit){
6051 uint8_t tmp;
6052 if(!contents || !*contents || !Value || !blimit){ return(0); }
6053 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(*contents, 1, blimit)( (sizeof(1) < sizeof(int) || (int)(1) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(*contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(*contents) >= (int)(1) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0); /* past end of buffer */
6054 if(**contents & U_TEST_INT70x80)return(0); /* this bit must be 0 in this object type */
6055 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(contents, &tmp, 1, 1, U_XE0);
6056 if(tmp & U_SIGN_INT70x40){
6057 tmp |= U_TEST_INT70x80; /* now it has the bit pattern of a signed int8_t */
6058 *Value = *(int8_t *)&tmp;
6059 }
6060 else {
6061 *Value = tmp;
6062 }
6063 return(1);
6064}
6065
6066/**
6067 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_INTEGER15 object
6068 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6069 \param contents Record from which to extract data
6070 \param Value 15 bit signed integer (stored in an integer)
6071 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6072
6073 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.22, Microsoft name: EmfPlusInteger15 Object
6074*/
6075int U_PMF_INTEGER15_get(const char **contents, U_FLOAT *Value, const char *blimit){
6076 if(!contents || !*contents || !Value || !blimit){ return(0); }
6077 uint16_t tmp;
6078 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(*contents, 2, blimit)( (sizeof(2) < sizeof(int) || (int)(2) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(*contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(*contents) >= (int)(2) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0); /* past end of buffer */
6079 if(!(**contents & U_TEST_INT70x80))return(0); /* this bit must be 1 in this object type */
6080 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(contents, &tmp, 2, 1, U_BE2);
6081 tmp &= U_MASK_INT150x7FFF; /* drop the 7/15 flag from the most significant bit */
6082 if(tmp & U_SIGN_INT150x4000){
6083 tmp |= U_TEST_INT150x8000; /* now it has the bit pattern of a signed int16_t */
6084 *Value = *(int16_t *)&tmp;
6085 }
6086 else {
6087 *Value = tmp;
6088 }
6089 return(1);
6090}
6091
6092/**
6093 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_LANGUAGEIDENTIFIER object
6094 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6095 \param LId U_PMF_LANGUAGEIDENTIFIER from which to extract data
6096 \param SubLId Example: code for USA
6097 \param PriLId Example: code for English
6098
6099
6100
6101 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.23, Microsoft name: EmfPlusLanguageIdentifier Object
6102
6103 This type is defined as 16 bits in the manual section, but it is only ever used as part of a 32 bit field!
6104*/
6105int U_PMF_LANGUAGEIDENTIFIER_get(U_PMF_LANGUAGEIDENTIFIER LId, int *SubLId, int *PriLId){
6106 if(!SubLId || !PriLId){ return(0); }
6107 *SubLId = (LId >> U_FF_SHFT_SUBLID0x000A ) & U_FF_MASK_SUBLID0x003F;
6108 *PriLId = (LId >> U_FF_SHFT_PRILID0x0000 ) & U_FF_MASK_PRILID0x03FF;
6109 /* 16 bits above that are not used */
6110 return(1);
6111}

6134/**
6135 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_LINEARGRADIENTBRUSHOPTIONALDATA object
6136 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6137 \param contents Record from which to extract data
6138 \param Flags BrushData flags - indicates which of the following date fields are present.
6139 \param Tm Transformation matrix
6140 \param Bc U_PMF_BLENDCOLORS object or NULL
6141 \param BfH U_PMF_BLENDFACTORS (H) object or NULL
6142 \param BfV U_PMF_BLENDFACTORS (V) object or NULL (WARNING, GDI+ defines this field but does not render it. DO NOT USE.)
6143 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6144
6145 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.25, Microsoft name: EmfPlusLinearGradientBrushOptionalData Object
6146
6147*/
6148int U_PMF_LINEARGRADIENTBRUSHOPTIONALDATA_get(const char *contents, uint32_t Flags, U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX *Tm,
6149 const char **Bc, const char **BfH, const char **BfV, const char *blimit){
6150 uint32_t Elements;
6151 if(!contents || !Tm|| !Bc || !BfH || !BfV || !blimit){ return(0); }
6152 /* all of the fields are optional! */
6153 *Bc = *BfH = *BfV = NULL((void*)0);
6154 if(Flags & U_BD_Transform0x0002){
6155 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_ROTMATRIX), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_ROTMATRIX)) < sizeof(int) || (int)(
sizeof(U_PMF_ROTMATRIX)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) >
(int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents
) >= (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_ROTMATRIX)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6156 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Tm, 4, 6, U_LE1);
6157 }
6158 if(Flags & U_BD_PresetColors0x0004){
6159 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, 4, blimit)( (sizeof(4) < sizeof(int) || (int)(4) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(4) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6160 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1); /* starts with a 4 byte count*/
6161 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, Elements * ( sizeof(U_FLOAT) + sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB)), blimit)( (sizeof(Elements * ( sizeof(U_FLOAT) + sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB)))
< sizeof(int) || (int)(Elements * ( sizeof(U_FLOAT) + sizeof
(U_PMF_ARGB))) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t
*)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >=
(int)(Elements * ( sizeof(U_FLOAT) + sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB))) ? 0
: 1 ))))return(0);
6162 contents-=4; /* back up to the front of the count, as it is part of the data field */
6163 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Bc, &contents, 0);
6164 }
6165 else if(Flags & U_BD_BlendFactorsH0x0008){
6166 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1); /* starts with a 4 byte count*/
6167 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT), blimit)( (sizeof(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < sizeof(int) ||
(int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6168 contents-=4; /* back up to the front of the count, as it is part of the data field */
6169 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(BfH, &contents, 4 + (Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT))); /* 4 byte count + 2 * 4bytes * Elements */
6170 if(Flags & U_BD_BlendFactorsV0x0010){
6171 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT), blimit)( (sizeof(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < sizeof(int) ||
(int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6172 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(BfV, &contents, 0);
6173 }
6174 }
6175 else if(Flags & U_BD_BlendFactorsV0x0010){
6176 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1); /* starts with a 4 byte count*/
6177 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT), blimit)( (sizeof(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < sizeof(int) ||
(int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(Elements * 2 * sizeof(U_FLOAT
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6178 contents-=4; /* back up to the front of the count, as it is part of the data field */
6179 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(BfV, &contents, 0);
6180 }
6181 return(1);
6182}

6248/**
6249 \brief Get data from a U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA object
6250 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6251 \param contents Record from which to extract data
6252 \param Pgbd constant part of U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA object
6253 \param Gradient variable part of U_PMF_LINEARGRADIENTBRUSHDATA, Color Gradient with Elements members
6254 \param Boundary variable part of U_PMF_LINEARGRADIENTBRUSHDATA, U_PMF_BOUNDARYPATHDATA object if BrushDataPath bit set in Flag, else U_PMF_BOUNDARYPOINTDATA object
6255 \param Data variable part of U_PMF_LINEARGRADIENTBRUSHDATA, exact composition depends on Flags
6256 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6257
6258 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.29, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPathGradientBrushData Object
6259
6260 Caller must check Data for possible memory access violations.
6261
6262*/
6263int U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA *Pgbd, const char **Gradient,
6264 const char **Boundary, const char **Data, const char *blimit){
6265 if(!contents || !Pgbd || !Gradient || !Boundary || !Data || !blimit){ return(0); }
6266 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, sizeof(U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA), blimit)( (sizeof(sizeof(U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA)) < sizeof(int
) || (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA)) < 0) ? 1 :
((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_PATHGRADIENTBRUSHDATA
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6267 uint32_t Size;
6268 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Pgbd, 4, 2, U_LE1); /* Flags and WrapMode*/
6269 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &(Pgbd->CenterColor), 4, 1, U_XE0);
6270 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &(Pgbd->Center), 4, 3, U_LE1); /* Center and Elements */
6271 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, Pgbd->Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB), blimit)( (sizeof(Pgbd->Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB)) < sizeof
(int) || (int)(Pgbd->Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB)) < 0
) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : (
(int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(Pgbd->
Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6272 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Gradient, &contents, Pgbd->Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_ARGB));
6273 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Boundary, &contents, 0);
6274 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &Size, 4, 1, U_LE1); /* The first 4 bytes of the Boundary are always a size */
6275 if(Pgbd->Flags & U_BD_Path0x0001){ contents += Size; } // U_PMF_BOUNDARYPATHDATA
6276 else { contents += Size*2*sizeof(U_FLOAT); } // U_PMF_BOUNDARYPOINTDATA
6277 if(Pgbd->Flags & (U_BD_Transform0x0002 |U_BD_PresetColors0x0004 | U_BD_BlendFactorsH0x0008| U_BD_FocusScales0x0040)){ // optional data present
6278 if(contents >= blimit)return(0); // the size is variable but this must still hold
6279 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Data, &contents, 0);
6280 }
6281 else { *Data = NULL((void*)0); } // no optional data present
6282 return(1);
6283}

6299 int varsize;

(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) -
(int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(4) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

6310 contents -= 4;
6311 varsize=(Elements * 4 * (Flags & U_BD_BlendFactorsH0x0008 ? 2 :1));
6312 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, varsize, blimit)( (sizeof(varsize) < sizeof(int) || (int)(varsize) < 0)

? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
6313 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Pattern, &contents, varsize);

6326 \return 1 on success, 0 on error

6329 \param Type PathPointType enumeration
6330 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6331
6332 EMF+ manual 2.2.2.31, Microsoft name: EmfPlusPathPointType Object
6333
6334 Note: order of 4bit fields appears to be shown in the LE column, not as
6335 documented in the BE column.
6336*/
6337int U_PMF_PATHPOINTTYPE_get(const char *contents, int *Flags, int *Type, const char *blimit){
6338 if(!contents || !Flags || !Type || !blimit){ return(0); }
6339 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, 1, blimit)( (sizeof(1) < sizeof(int) || (int)(1) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t

) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(1) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

6343 *Type = (tmp & U_PPT_MASK0x0F);
6344 return(1);

6532int U_PMF_POINTR_get(const char **contents, U_FLOAT *X, U_FLOAT *Y, const char *blimit){

6547/**
6548 \brief Get data from a variable POINTS object, which may be U_PMF_POINTS, U_PMF_POINTF, or U_PMF_POINTR.
6549 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
6550 \param contents Record from which to extract data
6551 \param Flags Record flags (bits U_PPF_C and U_PPF_P are referenced)
6552 \param Elements Number of points to retrieve.
6553 \param Points Caller must free. Array of U_PMF_POINTF coordinates.
6554 \param blimit one byte past the end of data
6555
6556 This function should never be called directly by end user code.
6557*/
6558int U_PMF_VARPOINTS_get(const char *contents, uint16_t Flags, int Elements, U_PMF_POINTF **Points, const char *blimit){
6559 int status = 0;
6560 if(!contents || !Points || !Elements || !blimit){ return(status); }
6561 U_PMF_POINTF *pts = (U_PMF_POINTF *)malloc(Elements * sizeof(U_PMF_POINTF));
6562 if(!pts){ return(status); }
6563 *Points = pts;
6564 U_FLOAT XF, YF;
6565 U_FLOAT XFS, YFS;
6566
6567 if(Flags & U_PPF_P0x0800){
6568 for(XFS = YFS = 0.0; Elements; Elements--, pts++){
6569 if(!U_PMF_POINTR_get(&contents, &XF, &YF, blimit))return(0); /* this should never happen */
6570 XFS += XF; /* position relative to previous point, first point is always 0,0 */
6571 YFS += YF;
6572 pts->X = XFS;
6573 pts->Y = YFS;
6574 }
6575 }
6576 else if(Flags & U_PPF_C0x4000){
6577 for(XF = YF = 0.0; Elements; Elements--, pts++){
6578 if(!U_PMF_POINT_get(&contents, &XF, &XF, blimit))break; /* this should never happen */
6579 pts->X = XF;
6580 pts->Y = YF;
6581 }
6582 }
6583 else {
6584 for(XF = YF = 0.0; Elements; Elements--, pts++){
6585 (void) U_PMF_POINTF_get(&contents, &XF, &YF, blimit);
6586 pts->X = XF;
6587 pts->Y = YF;
6588 }
6589 }
6590 if(Elements){ /* some error in the preceding */
6591 free(*Points);
6592 *Points = NULL((void*)0);
6593 }
6594 else {
6595 status = 1;
6596 }
6597 return(status);
6598}

6613 if(!contents

int)(sizeof(U_PMF_IE_COLORMATRIX)) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(
contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) -
(int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(sizeof(U_PMF_IE_COLORMATRIX
)) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);

7068/*
7069
7070 end of U_PMF_*_get() functions
7071 =====================================================================================
7072 start of U_PMR_*_get() functions
7073
7074 These functions all assume that the size field in the common EMF+ header has already
7075 been checked, so that the extent the record claims exists in the data read in for the file.
7076 Consequently none of them takes a blimit parameter. They generate a new one from the
7077 header size field and contents if needed.
7078
7079*/
7080
7081int U_PMR_common_stack_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header, uint32_t *StackID){
7082 if(!contents || !StackID){ return(0); }
7083
7084 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7085 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7086 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_RESTORE))return(0);
7087 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7088
7089 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, StackID, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7090 return(1);
7091}
7092
7093/* for records that have a type but no associated flag bits or data */
7094int U_PMR_common_header_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header){
7095 /* memory access safe, only uses the common header */
7096 if(!contents){ return(0); }
7097 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, Header);
7098 return(1);
7099}

7264/**
7265 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_HEADER record
7266 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7267 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7268 \param Header Common header (ignore flags)
7269 \param Version EmfPlusGraphicsVersion object
7270 \param IsDual set = Dual-mode file, clear= EMF+ only file.
7271 \param IsVideo set = video device, clear= printer. Ignore all other bits.
7272 \param LogicalDpiX Horizontal resolution reference device in DPI
7273 \param LogicalDpiY Vertical resolution reference device in DPI
7274
7275 EMF+ manual 2.3.3.3, Microsoft name: EmfPlusHeader Record, Index 0x01
7276*/
7277int U_PMR_HEADER_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7278 U_PMF_GRAPHICSVERSION *Version, int *IsDual, int *IsVideo, uint32_t *LogicalDpiX, uint32_t *LogicalDpiY){
7279 if(!contents || !Version || !IsDual || !IsVideo || !LogicalDpiX || !LogicalDpiY){ return(0); }
7280 uint32_t tmp;
7281
7282 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7283 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7284 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_HEADER))return(0);
7285 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7286
7287 *IsDual = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_DM0x0001 ? 1 : 0 );
7288 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Version, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7289 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, &tmp, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7290 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, LogicalDpiX, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7291 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, LogicalDpiY, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7292 *IsVideo = (tmp & U_PPF_VIDEO0x0001 ? 1 : 0 );
7293 return(1);
7294}

7318/**
7319 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_DRAWARC record
7320 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7321 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7322 \param Header Common header
7323 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
7324 \param ctype Set: int16_t coordinates; Clear: U_FLOAT coordinates
7325 \param Start Start angle, >=0.0, degrees clockwise from 3:00
7326 \param Sweep Sweep angle, -360<= angle <=360, degrees clockwise from Start
7327 \param Rect Caller must free. Bounding rectangle. Coordinate type set by ctype.
7328
7329 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.2, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawArc Record, Index 0x12
7330*/
7331int U_PMR_DRAWARC_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7332 uint32_t *PenID, int *ctype,
7333 U_FLOAT *Start, U_FLOAT *Sweep,
7334 U_PMF_RECTF *Rect){
7335 if(!contents || !PenID || !ctype || !Start || !Sweep || !Rect){ return(0); }
7336
7337 const char *blimit = contents;
7338 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7339 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7340 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_DRAWARC))return(0);
7341 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7342 blimit += lclHeader.Size;
7343
7344 *ctype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_C0x4000 ? 1 : 0 );
7345 *PenID = (lclHeader.Flags >> U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000) & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF;
7346 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Start, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7347 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Sweep, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7348 U_PMF_RECTF *Rects = NULL((void*)0);
7349 if(!U_PMF_VARRECTS_get(&contents, lclHeader.Flags, 1, &Rects, blimit))return(0);
7350 memcpy(Rect,Rects,sizeof(U_PMF_RECTF));
7351 free(Rects);
7352 return(1);
7353}

7356/**
7357 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS record
7358 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7359 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7360 \param Header Common header
7361 \param PenID U_PMF_PEN object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
7362 \param ctype Set: int16_t coordinates; Clear: U_FLOAT coordinates
7363 \param RelAbs Set: Coordinates are relative; Clear: Coordinates are absolute and their type is set by ctype
7364 \param Elements Number of members in the Data array
7365 \param Points Caller must free. Array of U_POINT_F = Sequence of points to connect. Coordinate type set by ctype and RelAbs.
7366
7367 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.3, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawBeziers Record, Index 0x19
7368*/
7369int U_PMR_DRAWBEZIERS_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7370 uint32_t *PenID, int *ctype, int *RelAbs,
7371 uint32_t *Elements,
7372 U_PMF_POINTF **Points){
7373 if(!contents || !PenID || !ctype || !RelAbs || !Elements || !Points){ return(0); }
7374
7375 const char *blimit = contents;
7376 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7377 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7378 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_DRAWBEZIERS))return(0);
7379 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7380 blimit += lclHeader.Size;
7381

7464/**
7465 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING record
7466 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7467 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7468 \param Header Common header
7469 \param FontID U_PMF_FONT object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
7470 \param btype Set: BrushID is an U_PFM_ARGB; Clear: index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in EMF+ object table.
7471 \param BrushID Color or index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table, depends on Flags bit0
7472 \param DSOFlags DriverStringOptions flags
7473 \param HasMatrix If 1 record contains a TransformMatrix field, if 0 it does not.
7474 \param Elements Number of members in Glyphs and Positions array
7475 \param Glyphs Caller must free. If U_DSO_CmapLookup is set in DSOFlags this is an array of UTF16LE characters, otherwise, it is an array of indices into the U_PMF_FONT object indexed by Object_ID in flags.
7476 \param Points Caller must free. Coordinates of each member of Glyphs. U_DSO_RealizedAdvance set in DSOFlags Relative then positions are calculated relative to the first glyph which is stored in Positions, otherwise, all glyph positions are stored in Positions.
7477 \param Matrix Caller must free. Transformation to apply to Glyphs & Positions. Present if HasMatrix is 1
7478
7479 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.6, Microsoft name: EmfPlusDrawDriverString Record, Index 0x36
7480*/
7481int U_PMR_DRAWDRIVERSTRING_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7482 uint32_t *FontID, int *btype,
7483 uint32_t *BrushID, uint32_t *DSOFlags, uint32_t *HasMatrix, uint32_t *Elements,
7484 uint16_t **Glyphs, U_PMF_POINTF **Points, U_PMF_TRANSFORMMATRIX **Matrix){
7485 if(!contents || !FontID || !btype || !BrushID ||
7486 !DSOFlags || !HasMatrix || !Elements || !Glyphs || !Points || !Matrix){ return(0); }
7487
7488 const char *blimit = contents;
7489 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7490 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7491 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_DRAWDRIVERSTRING))return(0);
7492 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7493 blimit += lclHeader.Size;
7494
7495 *btype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_B0x8000 ? 1 : 0 );
7496 *FontID = (lclHeader.Flags >> U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000) & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF;
7497 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, BrushID, 4, 1, (*btype ? U_XE0 : U_LE1)); /* color is not byte swapped, ID integer is */
7498 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, DSOFlags, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7499 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, HasMatrix, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7500 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7501 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, *Elements*2 + *Elements*2*4 + 24, blimit)( (sizeof(*Elements*2 + *Elements*2*4 + 24) < sizeof(int) ||
(int)(*Elements*2 + *Elements*2*4 + 24) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t
*)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit
) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int)(*Elements*2 + *Elements*
2*4 + 24) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
7502 if(!U_PMF_SERIAL_array_copy_get(&contents, (void **)Glyphs, 2, *Elements, U_LE1, (*DSOFlags & U_DSO_CmapLookup0x01))){ return(0); }
7503 if(!U_PMF_SERIAL_array_copy_get(&contents, (void **)Points, 4, *Elements *2, U_LE1, (*DSOFlags & U_DSO_RealizedAdvance0x04))){ return(0); }
7504 if(!U_PMF_SERIAL_array_copy_get(&contents, (void **)Matrix, 4, 6, U_LE1, (*HasMatrix))){ return(0); }
7505 return(1);
7506}

7777 if(IS_MEM_UNSAFE(contents, *Elements * 2, blimit)( (sizeof(*Elements * 2) < sizeof(int) || (int)(*Elements *
2) < 0) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(contents) > (int8_t *)(blimit
) ? 1 : ((int8_t *)(blimit) - (int8_t *)(contents) >= (int
)(*Elements * 2) ? 0 : 1 ))))return(0);
7778 if(!U_PMF_SERIAL_array_copy_get(&contents, (void **)String, 2, *Elements, U_XE0, 1)){ return(0); }
7779 return(1);
7780}

7782/**
7783 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_FILLCLOSEDCURVE record
7784 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7785 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7786 \param Header Common header
7787 \param btype Set: BrushID is an U_PFM_ARGB; Clear: is index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in EMF+ object table.
7788 \param ctype Set: int16_t coordinates; Clear: U_FLOAT coordinates
7789 \param ftype Set: winding fill; Clear: alternate fill
7790 \param RelAbs Set: Coordinates are relative; Clear: Coordinates are absolute and their type is set by ctype
7791 \param BrushID Color or index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table, depending on btype.
7792 \param Tension Controls splines, 0 is straight line, >0 is curved
7793 \param Elements Number of members in Points
7794 \param Points Caller must free. Array of U_POINT_F = Sequence of points to connect. Coordinate type set by ctype and RelAbs.
7795
7796 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.15, Microsoft name: EmfPlusFillClosedCurve Record, Index 0x16
7797*/
7798int U_PMR_FILLCLOSEDCURVE_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7799 int *btype, int *ctype, int *ftype, int *RelAbs,
7800 uint32_t *BrushID, U_FLOAT *Tension, uint32_t *Elements,
7801 U_PMF_POINTF **Points){
7802 if(!contents || !btype || !ctype || !ftype || !RelAbs || !BrushID || !Tension || !Elements || !Points){ return(0); }
7803
7804 const char *blimit = contents;
7805 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7806 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7807 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_DRAWLINES))return(0);
7808 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7809 blimit += lclHeader.Size;
7810
7811 *btype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_B0x8000 ? 1 : 0 );
7812 *ctype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_C0x4000 ? 1 : 0 );
7813 *ftype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_F0x2000 ? 1 : 0 );
7814 *RelAbs = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_P0x0800 ? 1 : 0 );
7815 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, BrushID, 4, 1, (*btype ? U_XE0 : U_LE1)); /* color is not byte swapped, ID integer is */
7816 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Tension, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7817 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7818 U_PMF_VARPOINTS_get(contents, lclHeader.Flags, *Elements, Points, blimit);
7819 return(1);
7820}

7956/**
7957 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_FILLRECTS record
7958 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
7959 \param contents Record from which to extract data
7960 \param Header Common header
7961 \param btype Set: BrushID is an U_PFM_ARGB; Clear: is index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in EMF+ object table.
7962 \param ctype Set: int16_t coordinates; Clear: U_FLOAT coordinates
7963 \param BrushID Color or index of U_PMF_BRUSH object in the EMF+ object table, depending on btype.
7964 \param Elements Number of members in Data.
7965 \param Rects Caller must free. Array of U_PMF_RECTF rectangles to draw.
7966
7967 EMF+ manual 2.3.4.20, Microsoft name: EmfPlusFillRects Record, Index 0x0A
7968
7969 EMF+ files have been encountered where BrushID must be a color, because it has a value like FFFF0000 but
7970 the flags are set wrong, so that U_PPF_B is not set. Detect these by BrushID >63 for btype=0 and correct.
7971 If the opposite problem occurs it cannot be reliably detected, so it cannot be corrected.
7972
7973 Rects in record may be either U_PMF_RECT or U_PMF_RECTF, but this function always
7974 returns U_PMF_RECTF
7975*/
7976int U_PMR_FILLRECTS_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
7977 int *btype, int *ctype,
7978 uint32_t *BrushID, uint32_t *Elements,
7979 U_PMF_RECTF **Rects){
7980 if(!contents || !btype || !ctype || !BrushID || !Elements || !Rects){ return(0); }
7981
7982 const char *blimit = contents;
7983 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
7984 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
7985 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_FILLRECTS))return(0);
7986 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
7987 blimit += lclHeader.Size;
7988
7989 *btype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_B0x8000 ? 1 : 0 );
7990 *ctype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_C0x4000 ? 1 : 0 );
7991 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, BrushID, 4, 1, (*btype ? U_XE0 : U_LE1)); /* color is not byte swapped, ID integer is */
7992 U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, Elements, 4, 1, U_LE1);
7993 U_PMF_VARRECTS_get(&contents, lclHeader.Flags, *Elements, Rects, blimit);
7994 /* correct btype, if necessary, for invalid EMF+ input */
7995 if((*BrushID > 63) & !*btype)*btype=1;
7996 return(1);
7997}

8028
8029/**
8030 \brief Get data from a U_PMR_OBJECT record
8031 \return 1 on success, 0 on error
8032 \param contents Record from which to extract data
8033 \param Header Common header
8034 \param ObjID Index for this object in the EMF+ object table (0-63, inclusive)
8035 \param otype ObjectType enumeration
8036 \param ntype Set: object definition continue bit is set
8037 \param TSize If ntype is set, holds the total number of data bytes split across multiple records. If ntype is clear, has no meaning.
8038 \param Data Object's data. Type from otype.
8039
8040 EMF+ manual 2.3.5.1, Microsoft name: EmfPlusObject Record, Index 0x13
8041
8042 Caller must check Data for possible memory access violations.
8043
8044 OTHER NOTES:
8045 All objects are to be stored in the same table and retrieved by index.
8046 Documentation indicates that this table contains only 64 slots, although the index
8047 field which references it can code for values 0-127.
8048 If a new object has the same index as an existing object the old one is deleted and
8049 the new one goes into its storage slot.
8050 The continuation bit (U_PPF_N) is documented as indicating that the object is continued into
8051 the next record. Examination of emf+ records in emf files produced by PowerPoint 2003
8052 show that changing the ObjID also serves as a continued record terminator, and that it apparently
8053 overrides the value for the continue bit. That is, even though the preceding records said
8054 that it was continued, the change of ObjID terminates that preceding record without adding
8055 any more data to it. In one example the sequential emf+ records were:
8056 ObjID type size continue
8057 0 5 65008 Y
8058 0 5 65008 Y
8059 0 5 63104 Y
8060 1 8 24 N
8061 A DrawImagePoints record followed that referenced ObjID 0.
8062 Examination of the records with continue set showed that data in each
8063 was preceded by a uint32_t size value equivalent to the size of the
8064 data that had been split across multiple records, in this case
8065 0x0002F254 = 193108. It is not clear at present if this size value
8066 will also be present at the end of a continued series that terminates
8067 by not using the continue bit, rather than changing the ObjID.
8068*/
8069int U_PMR_OBJECT_get(const char *contents, U_PMF_CMN_HDR *Header,
8070 uint32_t *ObjID, int *otype, int *ntype, uint32_t *TSize,
8071 const char **Data){
8072 if(!contents || !ObjID || !otype || !ntype || !Data){ return(0); }
8073
8074 U_PMF_CMN_HDR lclHeader;
8075 U_PMF_CMN_HDR_get(&contents, &lclHeader);
8076 if(lclHeader.Size < sizeof(U_PMF_OBJECT))return(0);
8077 if(Header){ memcpy(Header,&lclHeader,sizeof(U_PMF_CMN_HDR)); }
8078
8079 *ntype = (lclHeader.Flags & U_PPF_N0x8000 ? 1 : 0 );
8080 *ObjID = (lclHeader.Flags >> U_FF_SHFT_OID80x0000) & U_FF_MASK_OID80x00FF;
8081 *otype = (lclHeader.Flags >> U_FF_SHFT_OT0x0008) & U_FF_MASK_OT0x003F;
8082 if(*ntype){ U_PMF_SERIAL_get(&contents, TSize, 4, 1, U_LE1); }
8083 else { *TSize = 0; }
8084 U_PMF_PTRSAV_SHIFT(Data, &contents, 0);
8085 return(1);
8086}
8087
